Score each task by a weighted rule such as priority = impact × confidence / effort, then rank by that score.
A sensible ordering is: (1) formalise the reusable core lemma library, because it unlocks many downstream proofs with high confidence; (2) formalise the main theorem once the dependencies exist, because its impact is high but execution risk is higher; (3) formalise peripheral corollaries last, because their marginal impact is lowest.
This gives a roadmap that maximises reusable value early while keeping delivery risk controlled.
